betterquesting:10.desc:8: You won't survive by just mindlessly running around. Plant some crops if you want to keep living. Also, maybe, just maybe you should get a bed
§c§rIn this world it's often kill or be killed. If you're not fighting back you're already dead.
You need some tools to survive in this world
Those stone tools won't be enough.

This is the best you're going to get by conventional means. You're now ready to branch out into some other profession. §6§4
If you're looking for better tools, maybe try smithing §6or ignore that previous statement and go for engineering. It's better than that §r§r§6§oparticular§r§6 outdated technology.
§7§1Or ignore both of them and just leave this entire world behind.
Now that you're able to get by, I think it's a good time to get some necessary resources now.

Sometimes, plants just aren't enough...
Also, this is your last task here, so let's talk a bit about your future.
§c§2Maybe becoming a herbalist might interest you as a survivor. It's more rewarding than you think, give it a try.
§
§cOr.... you could take the only right option and become a sorcerer and maybe even try messing around with the forbidden arts.
Now that you're done with the easy targets, you're ready to take on something §oslightly§r more challenging.

Time to take on the strongest targets you'll find here.
§5Maybe it's time to continue your yourney in another dimension when you're done here...
No Description

§5Well, you've slain the monsters of the Overworld. This may be the start of a wonderful journey across different realms for you, if you're up to the challenge. I'll always be here to guide you, 90% of the time.

3:10.command:8: /say VAR_NAME is now starting a journey across dimensions

betterquesting:10.desc:8: §4You'll need a bunch of those bricks if you want to get started as a blacksmith
§4Get started building your smeltery.
§4Create your first cast for ingots
§4Prepare the casts for your first own custom tool
§5The Naga found in the forest starts out pretty large and long, but once you wear it down a bit, it will start losing parts of its body, making it smaller and unfortunately also faster.
§4What will happen when you combine those Nether ores?
§4Craft a few tables and stations and so on since you'll need them to build tools.
§4Prepare the casts for your first own custom weapon.
§4Enjoy your massive damage.
§4§4Sometimes, a simple pickaxe isn't enough...
§4Of course you found out this one exists. You're really going to build that weapon aren't you? I don't even want to give you a "reward" for completing this to be honest.
§4Yes, there's a follow up. Yes, there's a decent reward for it. Yes, I regret creating this quest.

§4§5You may think this world's equivalent of heaven would be nice, but it's actually a bit worse than hell.

§1This place shouldn't exist. It's above the clouds, yet you can't see it from outer space.

§5But it does, end of discussion.

§§§1Sure, if you don't want to talk about it, I'll just leave.

§5*sigh*
§5It's been a while since the last time I visited the forest, but I don't think the monsters there have gotten any friendlier since last time. If anything, they're even deadlier now.

§6Why rely on oldhat, boring magic when you can just program magic instead?§6

Put the Assembly into the Assembler to create your first CAD.
§5§5Welcome to the Nether, it's basically the hell of this world and as you'd probably expect there's going to be a lot of lava down there.
§5Your final destination?

§5Only a dead dragon is a good dragon.

§2Is this senseless killing really necessary?

§5In this case it is.

§2But why?

§5Because it benefits whoever completes this quest.

§2Sure, but does this really justify killing it?

§5From my perspective it absolutely does, NOW STOP INTERRUPTING MY QUESTLINE ALREADY!

§2...ok, I'm out.

§5*sigh* he knows the rules of this world, there's no point in not killing th§c§5- §cHAVE I HEARD KILLING?

§5Yes, and before you ask, yes I approve it.

§cGood, good. Then there's no reason for me to be here, bye.

§5*sigh* one interruption is already annoying, but two are a step too far.

§5
§5The dragon is dead, time to slay his henchmen. Of course you'll be rewarded for it eventually.
§5The Queen will probably be a little bit angry that you've killed her underlings in order to reach her. She sure as hell won't let you win easily.
§5I thought fiery creatures are only found in the Nether... Maybe the Aether is close to the sun than I originally assumed.
§5Just a block randomly sliding across the room? Shouldn't be a problem for you, right?
§5§5Good job killing the different boss monsters up there. Now go on and slay some of those flying annoyances. The less there are, the better for you.
§5Ghasts are the main reason why I avoid visiting the Nether. §5You'd do me a favor if you would kill their queen.

§5Well, you'll need to create this atrocity yourself, but the reward is more than worth it. Just don't build it anywhere near your home...§2

§6I'm pretty sure you could automatically build those. You just have to choose the right profession (it's Engineer by the way).

§5Could you please just STOP promoting yourself in MY questline?

§6NEVER!

§5*sigh* Am I the only reasonable one here?
§5A common ore found in the Nether. Looks great as a decoration, but it wouldn't be my first choice for tools and weapons.
§5You'll need a lot of it for Aether enchantments, so collect as many as you can
§5A kind of gem found in the Aether. You'll need this for an altar and it's also a decent material for weapons and armor.
§5An ore that floats upward? Interesting...
§4Shooting your enemies from afar isn't as risky as running into them, obviously. Getting a good bow or crossbow will surely make life easier for you.
§4Well, you're now able to create advanced tools. You can trade me one of your hammers in exchange for Heart Shards if you like.
§4Would you mind creating a longbow for me? Didn't get to use one in a while y'know.
§4I'd really like an oversized sword right now. Would you mind giving me one?
§4You'll need an Ancient Codex, otherwise you won't have a clue what you're doing with those cores.
§5There's nothing quite like ripping and tearing through the creatures of hell...
§5Pretty good material for tools created in a smeltery. If you happen to be or know a blacksmith, you might be able to create some really powerful tools.
§5Doesn't attack and mine as fast as cobalt, but creates one of the strongest alloys for weapons when combined with cobalt.

§cAll hostile creatures have a demonic will inside. What better way to make use of it than ripping it out of their body with a snare?

Get the Hellfire Forge too while you're at it since you'll need it to use the demonic will you'll collect.
§cJust sprinkle it on some blocks and maybe something interesting might happen.
§cAren't those individual Demonic Wills cluttering your inventory a bit annoying? Better store them in a tartaric gem instead.
§1Some other machines that will surely prove useful at some point.
§cSacrifice your own blood to the altar to get started. Might need a special dagger to stab yourself with...
§c§cHow about stabbing yourself just a little bit harder? The Incense Altar allows for just that. It brings you down to one health after stabbing yourself one time.

§1Alright, before we can even think about reaching the orbit, we need some electric energy first. Build yourself a little dynamo, a fluxduct and an energy cell to get started. Also, getting a wrench at this point might help too.
§1Just the basics for now. You're at a severe technological disadvantage if you can't smelt items with RF and double your ore output.
§1Just the normal Fluxducts from before won't suffice forever. Also, maybe you'll want to automatically transport items and fluids since doing so manually is just annoying.
§4You'll need them later and I'm too lazy to explain what they're needed for right now. I'll tell you when they're relevant.

§4That's where the Atmospheric Gauge from before comes into play. It shows you where large amounts of Embers can be found. However, the Ember-density changes over time, so don't expect one good spot to constantly farm tons of Ember. The Bore has to be placed in a 3x3 space closely above the bedrock and needs to be fuel in the form of coal, which can be inserted with pipes. Extractors can be easily powered by levers by the way.
§4I'll need some of those Embers you collected for my own experiments. Mind handing some of them over?
§5A summoner of the undead? Surely you can deal with that little inconvenience, right?
§5Don't even bother slaying the heads, there will only grow more in its place if you cut them off.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Part Cow, Part Shroom, Part Man
betterquesting:10.desc:8: §5At least this one does way less damage than the hydra and the lich.
§5As you may have already noticed, I despise Ghasts. SO PLEASE KILL IT ALREADY!!!
§5Just so you're prepared: there are six of them.
§5Better put those Yetis back in place and also kill their leader while you're at it.
§5Those glaciers weren't around the last time I visited. Find the creature at their core and ideally get rid of it.

§5You've already slain all the bo§c§5s§c§5- §cWHY NOT KILL SOME MORE?!?

§5This is MY questline, why are you invading he§5- §cCome on, just let me have some fun!

§5*sigh* Ok, enjoy messing with this one quest as long as you don't even think about touching the others... bye.

§cNow then, the new official description for this quest is: "go ahead and kill those bosses!"
§6§6§6Drop a piece of redstone and use your CAD on it to infuse it with psyonic energy which results in the creation of Psidust.
§6You can even create armor out of Psimetal, which may prove useful...

§2In order to get started with Astrology, you'll need a tome, which will serve as your guide. Also, it's important to explore and find shrines which contain constellation papers that can be added to your tome. You'll need to discover constellations in order to use their powers.
§Y§6You'll need a spell programmer and bullets for it to make use of the CAD's full potential. Also, while you're at it create the parts for a proper CAD.

§6§6You can cast transformation spells you created on the spell programmer to create more materials for stronger CADs. You'll need the tricks "Infusion", "Greater Infusion" and "Ebony And Ivory" to create these.
§6§6The standard components for CADs are fine, but you can easily do a little better. You'll be able to code and execute more versatile spells with them.

§Y§4You need to insert the Embers you received from the bore into an activator via pipes in order to use the energy stored within them. To save the energy, you have to transfer it to a copper cell with an Ember Emitter. Now you'll need that hammer from two quests ago to connect the Emitter and Receptor.
§Y§1You could probably live without these, but whatever. There's no harm in having them around.
§1Just some helpful little devices. They collect water, destroy unneeded items and increase the working speed of adjecent machines.
§4Don't know why you need a centrifuge instead of just melting them together like other alloys. Anyway, if you could do it the easy way§5§r§4, giving you a reward for it wouldn't feel right.

§4In order to use Ember-powered tools you'll need some way to store Ember in your inventory. Either you go for a cartridge, which stores a lot of Ember, but takes up a slot in your inventory or you go for a bulb, which stores significantly less, but can be worn anywhere on your body.
§4Ember-powered tools are great. They don't break, do a lot of damage and are overall pretty useful. However, if you run out of Ember they're complete useless.
§4I don't think there's a better way to use Ember than just directly shooting it at your enemies.
§4To augment your tools, weapons and armor you need to hammer a motive core into them on a dawnstone anvil.
§§§4Makes your Ember-powered weapons just a little bit stronger. It's awesome and you definitely want it.
§4Straightforward upgrades for your tools and weapons. They even work on stuff you made in the Smeltery.
§4So far we only cared about weapons and tools, but armor is important too... I guess

§4Once you've built up enough heat in the motive core you can toss the item and some Ember crystals into the forge to give it a new upgrade slot for augments. Naturally, the forge needs to be powered by Ember from below.
§2Even more options. I think we're finally getting somewhere.
§2But wait, there's more.
§2You can even create diamonds and emeralds with these. Aren't they great?§2
§2These will open up a few more options for crops.
§2Better crafting seeds give you more options for different crops.
§a§2These seeds will potentially allow you to farm everything you want. Ok, maybe not everything, but at least a ton of different things.
§2Now use these seeds and farm some essences.
§2More essences, more rewards§2.
§2Finally, essences that can be used for valuable resources.
§2§2§2Now those are useful essences. Ok, admittedly you could also create some resources with the previous ones, but these are just straight up better.
§2DIAMONDS!!! (and emeralds too)
§4Wouldn't it be nice if those ember-powered tools and weapons would use their energy just a little bit more efficiently?
§4§4There's nothing wrong with getting just a little drunk, y'know.

§4§4a<lowixm<laWAIOmxaeoyöWAW WOE A UXNMI;XOWOEIAWIXEW_A_ÄY_ÄWA_XEYAOXOOWAOYOW:XXWAJICNGAWK X X;LAIW :UXAEX!"=COAWI;XOOMHHUWZ!O("SD!" IDOA/"()$

§r§6HEY! What's that even supposed to mean? You're drunk again, aren't you?

§6Alright, seems like I have to hand out the rewards then since your "boss" doesn't seem capable of saying anything comprehensible right now.
§4Isn't that the kind of stuff an alchemist would do? Anyway, it's occasionally useful, so we'll utilize it.

§b§4Sigh, I'll let §ohim§r§4 explain this one.

§b§cAlright then, you'll need Aspecti on pedestals near the tablet before you blast it with the beam cannon. Also, they need a bunch of ash to function properly and you'll probably need to try various amounts of ash until you find the right dose for the exchange to work. The alchemical waste will show how far you were off.

§4...I didn't understand any of this, but thanks.

§cThis will be the last time I'll help you out and the only time I'll ever be nice. I'm out!
§6Just set the bedrock on fire and with a bit of luck you'll get grains of infinity, which are necessary for building a machine chassis.
§6You know, these simple devices constantly leak energy, but you'll need to use them to build the actual machines.
§6Now that the simple machines are up and running, you can build versions of them that DON'T CONSTANTLY LOSE ENERGY. But they'll also need capacitors.
§6Usually, I don't care about the environment, but since solar panels only require sunlight to produce energy, I support their use.
§6Can't go wrong with stronger photovoltaic cells.
§6§6How about upgrading these things even further?
§6Alright, these are the best you're going to get.
§6What use is your energy if you can't even store it?
§6You could just place a bunch of adjecent capacitor banks to get the same result as with this better bank, but at some point they would take up too much space.
§6Filling up such a huge capacitor bank might take a while...
§6How about some stronger capacitors? They increase the working speed of your machines and also increase their internal energy storage.
§6Even stronger capacitors? Sure, go for it!
§6You already have functional machines that don't leak energy... how about building better ones even if it's unnecessary?
§6Maybe you need a bit more than just SAG Mills and Alloy Smelters.
§6Not to confuse with Power Armor. Anyway, when combined with vibrant crystals these are able to store energy and have different modules installed.
§6You need some sort of cables, right? Well, conduits not only function as such, they can also be placed on the same block, meaning that your constructions will end up being really compact.
§6Want to transport more energy at the same time? Want to transport multiple fluids through the same conduit? Sure you do!
§6You won't ever manage to send this much energy through one conduit anyway.
§6Great, your machines are capable of storing more energy than a normal capacitor bank with this.
§6Your empowered armor needs to be charged if you want to use its special functions.
§6Why walk if you can just TELEPORT instead?
§1Once you upgrade your machines with this, you can install augments to change their functionality or increase their effectiveness.
§6ME Systems are one of the most capable and effective storage methods. To get started, you'll need to gather inscriber presses from meteors.
§6You guessed it, there's a machine you need to build in order to use the presses.

§6To build a functional ME System you need a terminal, cable, storage drive and most importantly, an ME Controller. Also, an Energy Acceptor to connect it to your existing power sources will be necessary.
§6Maybe, you want to keep some parts of your inventory private...
§6It'll take a while to fill up this much storage just with items.
§6Get the largest capacity spatial storage available.
§6How do you even fit fluids into a disk drive without breaking the entire thing? It's probably for the best if you don't question it and just use it while it works.

§6The ME System is fine as it is, but you should build an import and export bus to be able to connect the massive storage at your disposal with the rest of your machines. Also, they're a bit slow normally, so you might want to accelerate the process a bit.
§1These two augments are always useful, no matter what machine they're installed on.
§1With this you can install up to 4 augments in your machines. It may be a bit excessive, but if you've got the resources to do it, just go for it.
§7Ok, get the casts for the hammer and you're almost ready to head down into the mines and start the excavation.
§7The Fluxbore is a drill that can be upgraded multiple times. It always requires a bunch of RF to function so make sure to regularly charge it.
§7The Infinity Drill might just be the strongest mining tool out there, but you need to charge it for an eternity until it starts getting useful.
§7Get some bricks for a smeltery. You'll need them if you want to get to business.
§4§7Build a smeltery and you'll soon be ready to mine.
§7§7§7§6§7§7Cobalt has the fastest base mining speed, make sure to put it to good use. When you're done here, build the hammer and start mining already.
§7With this upgrade the Fluxbore is able to rival hammers since its mining area is increased to 3x3.
§7Doesn't increase the mining area, but you need it to create the next version of the Fluxbore anyway.
§73x3x3! Finally, it starts getting useful.
§7Now you got yourself the strongest Fluxbore available. Time to head down into the mine and farm a ton of ores.

§1If you want to reach the orbit, you'll need to be able to create wafers and compressed plates, since they are necessary to build rockets and advanced machinery that is necessary for surviving in space.
§1It's a pipe that transports humans and apparently it surpasses the normal movement or even flying speed. Not as fast as teleportation for obvious reasons, but way cooler,

§1You'll need a special crafting table to construct an entire rocket and a way to refine oil into rocket fuel. Keep in mind that you can extract oil from coal and charcoal blocks in the Magma Crucible if you don't find enough of it in your world.
§1You know, humans aren't able to just survive without an atmosphere. Better bring some oxygen or you'll die. miserably.

§1Now onto building the rocket and actually launching it into SPAAACE!!!

Please bring a fuel loader and your oxygen producing machines, otherwise you might get stuck far away from the overworld.
§1§1This is the only location you can reach for now (except for space stations) and you'll need some materials from there to build sturdier rockets.
§1Landing in an Asteroid field is really risky. Are you sure you want to do this? On the other hand, there should be some rare metals that could make this trip worth it.
§1After a visit to the moon you may or may not be able to build a tier 2 rocket, which is able to finally reach a new planet and not just the moon.
§1Are you sure you want to go there? Seems a bit too hot for me.

§1You can get meteoric iron from the meteors occasionally landing on the moon. You'll need it to reinforce heavy duty plates and build stronger rockets. Apparently there are dungeons on the moon where you can get a shematic for better rockets.
§3§1Now that you have gathered some meteoric iron, you should be able to build a rocket that takes you to another planet.
§1New dungeon, new schematic. If I'm not mistaken it should allow you to reach even more distant locations in our solar system. Also, you'll need some desh to build the necessary heavy duty plates.
§1This is the strongest conventional rocket we'll ever be able to build. We should hopefully be able to reach a new planet with this.
§1CHEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEESE!!!
§1Mind giving me some of this new metal? Might need some of it should I ever want to go to hostile locations like Venus.
§§§1I need a few volcanic rocks for research purposes. You might want to dig those up with a silk touch pickaxe because otherwise they'll burst into flowing lava after you break them.
§1A rare and really sturdy metal usually found on asteroids? Might have some uses for this...

§6§2Biofuel §c-or proteins, which one do you prefer.

§6Guys, keep your discussions out of my quest line. I'll just make it necessary to get both generators.
§6Unlimited natural resources, at least as long as you provide enough energy to keep this massive Laser Drill running.

§2For the creation of useful plants and items, runes will be necessary. To build them, a runic altar will be necessary. This altar requires a decent amount of mana to function, so you'll have to point a mana spreader at it.
§2For now we'll create a simple setup to deliver mana from a generating flower like the Endoflame to a mana pool.
§2Placing an Alchemy Catalyst below your mana pools allows you to transmute a few materials into others by tossing them into the mana pool. For example, you can create nether warts from blaze rods.

§2Terrasteel is an immensely powerful material and can be used to create tools, swords and armor. Creating it is sadly no simple task, since it requires a specific structure, mana infused resources and a huge amount of mana to create.

§2Creating a gateway to Alfheim allows you to trade with elves, but the connection sadly isn't strong enough to let humans pass through. Anyway, it allows you to obtain some unique materials. The gateway needs to be powered by two pylons, which need to be placed on top of the mana pools they should drain from.

§2In order to obtain spirits of Gaia, which are necessary for abvanced baubles and a few other items you have to summon and defeat the Guardian of Gaia. For this you will need a beacon, pylons and a terrasteel ingot to start the fight. The fight won't be easy, so better prepare yourself and maybe get some others to fight by your side.
§2Since I'm not able to defeat the Guardian myself while I'm stuck in this quest log, I'd appreciate it if you could hand me some Gaia Spirits.
§2The gear created from terrasteel can easily surpass the strength of typical diamond gear and will surely make fights against stronger monsters easier.
§2Ever wanted an undead horse? Well, now you can. Infecting it with one of these viruses turns it into either a zombie or skeleton horse.
§2This terrasteel may not help much in my current situation, but stacking up on it for the occasion that I can leave this quest log wouldn't be the worst idea I had so far.
§2Apparently, this item's name includes the German word for wing, so I'm not surprised that it allows you to fly. At a decent cost of mana, naturally...

§2You know, just transforming items with mana would be fine, but it only starts getting fun once you create flowers that make good use of your mana. These ones right here for example can create ores, mystical flowers or heat at the cost of some mana.
§2Quite a few items created from mana infused materials require mana to be used effectively or repair themselves. For this purpose, you can fill mana tablets at your mana pools.
§2It's possible to create several rings that give you specific effects when worn. For example there are ones that increase your reach or allow you to store mana like a tablet.
§2With the Gaia Spirits dropped by the guardian you can build some baubles with powerful effects. Among them are some really fashionable clothes that you should get regardless of their effects.

§2Apparently, you can summon a stronger Guardian of Gaia if you use a Gaia Spirit ingot instead of terrasteel. Defeating this guardian gives you a dice which will grant you want one of six special relics.
§2§1§2You won't get far if you don't know what you're doing. That's why I'm stuck in your quest log, I didn't know what I was doing either.
§2You can easily create your own plants with the apothecary if you toss in the right petals and a seed to finish the process.

§2To create the items necessary for mana manipulation, you'll need livingwood and livingrock. These are created by placing logs and stone respectively around a Pure Daisy, which can be created in the apothecary.
§1Just a little drill that can be upgraded further. Trust me, you won't regret investing in it.
§1The Fluxbore from before was alright, I guess, but once you upgrade it, it gets really helpful since it's mining area increases.
§6§6§6You know, I usually don't ask for something like this, but could you please give me some of these storage cells?
§6I don't like asking for stuff like this, but could you please get me some capacitors? I really need some of my own machines to work faster.
§1§1§1§6§1§r§1Would you mind getting me one of these conversion kits? They allow you to upgrade your machines to the highest level immediately.

§2With the help of a runic altar you can create rods capable of performing various abilities at the cost of some mana. This allows you among others to create light bridges, propell yourself into the air or terraform.§2

§2To harness the power of starlight you will need a luminous crafting table. It needs to be placed in the open to access the starlight and the crafting process can only be finished by a resonating wand.

§1§3§2If there isn't enough starlight in your area to craft specific items, you can gain it by building a spectral relais multiblock structure near your crafting table. The exact layout can be found in the tome.
§2By putting aquamarine, resonating gems or rock crystals into a lightwell, which is placed under the night sky, you can create liquid starlight, which may have some uses later on.
§2It's nice to know how constellations look like, but that alone won't help if you haven't spotted them yet. To find constellations you'll need a looking glass.

§2This table is a direct upgrade to the your previous crafting table, but it will no longer work once you build it since it requires a specific structure of marble around it to function. Check your tome for further information.
§1§2The Telescope functions similarly to the looking glass, but it allows you to spot more distant constellations and is stationary.

§2The observatory allows you to discover a few new faint constellations. It works just like the looking glass. These new constellations can only be attuned to already attuned crystals, which alters the effect of the previously attuned constellation.
§2Well, now that you've got your altar up and running you can create some wands that help you move around and build more efficiently.

§2§1Hey, shouldn't you theoretically be able to use these to travel between planets?

§2Yeah, I guess, but you'll still need to build one on the planet you want to reach, so you can't just skip the entire trip.

§1Damn, seems like I still have to rely on these old-fashioned rockets then.
§2You remember those floating crystals sometimes found in shrines, right? Apparently you can link them to a lens and direct their starlight into your altar.
§2Bigger and better than the previous one, but needs a new structure built around it.

§2With the attunement altar and its required structure you can attune yourself to a constellation you have discovered. This grants you special perks that may increase your mining speed, combat capabilities, movement, etc. Once you're attuned you can also learn new constellations from papers. Additionally, you can attune rock crystals, which grants them some special effects when placed on a pedestal.

§2You can create celestial crystals by tossing rock crystals and stardust into a pool of liquid starlight. This will create a cluster, which takes a while to grow, but in the end gives you a celestial crystal, which can have far better stats than a rock crystal ever could.

§2The Starlight Infuser, as the name implies, allows you to infuse items and weapons with starlight. The structure requires liquid starlight, which is consumed in the process, meaning that you need to refill it if you don't want the structure to just stop working.

§2At your new altar you can manually create the floating crystals you've seen in shrines before. Their effectiveness at gathering starlight depends on their stats, so choose ones with decent size, purity and cut for this process.
§2I don't know if I can even use any of these crystals, but that doesn't stop me from giving you rewards for trading them to me.
§2The Celestial Altar will allow you to craft another wand, which is capable of turning solid blocks into transparent, glowing variations of themselves.

§2This will be the last upgrade for your crafting altar and you'll gain access to quite a few new recipes through it. Naturally, you'll need to change the structure around it again in order for it to work. This one additionally requires you to place items in relais around the altar for some recipes.

§2With your new altar you're able to create the Mantle of the Stars, which can be attuned to different constellations for special effects and enchanted like normal armor. This makes the mantle way stronger than your average chestplate.
§2You're now capable of upgrading your resonating wand and with your iridescent alter. However, you'll need a second wand to activate the altar, since your first is part of the recipe.
§2Hey, I'd love to get one of these mantles for myself, but sadly there doesn't seem to be any starlight within this quest log, so could you please create one for me? Vicio in particular seems nice.
§cWell, you'll need to slaughter a lot of monsters to collect enough Demonic Will for this gem. §oGO FOR IT!
§cJust capable of storing quite a lot more Demonic Will.
§cYou know what's just as annoying as having a ton of demonic will in your inventory? Having to snare every hostile creature. Just deliver the killing blow with a Sentient Sword instead.

§cYou can upgrade your Blood Altar to tier II by placing 8 runes on the floor around it which gives you access to new recipes. There are further upgrades, but I can't trace them from this quest log, so you won't get any rewards directly after upgrading.
§cThink your sacrifices aren't valued enough? Think your altar doesn't store enough blood? Well, some special runes can help if that's the case...
§cStash some blood within your own network to use it for powering bound items or sigils or whatever.
